The mother of a 12-year-old Florida girl who jumped to her death after being bullied for months is exploring her legal options.

Attorneys said Thursday that they haven't yet taken legal action on behalf of Rebecca Sedwick's mother, Tricia Norman. However, they didn't ruled out suing Polk County schools or the parents of two girls who were arrested in connection with Sedwick's death.

Norman and her attorneys spoke today at a press conference after an attorney for one of the girls, 14-year-old Guadalupe Shaw, entered a written not-guilty plea on her behalf.

