Shaw will next appear in court on October 29 for a pretrial conference.

According to the Orlando Sentinel, Norman hired prominent law firm Morgan & Morgan to review the evidence for possible civil suits.

Among the attorneys representing Rebecca Sedwick's mother, Tricia Norman, is former Governor Charlie Crist.

Norman's attorneys said at a news conference today that they plan to establish a website to help her raise money to pay for funeral costs. Any additional funds will be used for anti-bullying causes.

Two of Sedwick's schoolmates, Shaw and 12-year-old Katelyn Roman, who deputies say were primarily responsible for the bullying, were arrested last week.

They were charged with stalking.

